First of all, best wishes for Navratri 2020 to all of you. During the 9 days of holy festival of Navratri, nine forms of Goddess Durga are worshiped and each day is dedicated to an incarnation of Goddess Mother. As we all know, there are different forms of Goddess. Today is the first of the auspicious nine days of Navratri which is dedicated to Goddess Shailaputri.Shailaputri, daughter of the mountains, is a avatar of the goddess, Durga. She is one of the first Navadurga venerated during the first day of Navratri. She is also known as Sati, Bhavani, Parvati or Hemavati.Shailaputri mata ( #shailputrimata ) is the absolute form of Mother Nature. Mata Shailputri is born from a rock or a mountain, so worshiping her brings stability in life. With proper worship of Mata Shailputri, marital life remains happy and happiness comes to your family. Their archana awakens the muladhara chakra, which results in the development of vitality and enthusiasm in life. At the same time, on the first day of Navratri, by worshiping mother Shailaputri, all kinds of defects associated with the moon are removed and good fortune is achieved.  We should listen #navratrikatha of maa Shailputri  on day 1 of navratri for her blessings. Maa Shailputri ki katha shows who is devi shailputri. How devi got this name of Shailputri ? This video also shows Shailputri Aarti, shailputri mantra , shailputri kavach, and shailputri stotram.

So, get your daily dose of laughter with Jethalal, Taarak Mehta, Daya, Champaklal and their neighbors in Gokuldham Society.About Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah:--------------------------------------------------------------------The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story revolves around daily happenings in Gokuldham Co-operative Society and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Shailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi / Raj Anadkat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. This story revolves around daily happenings in Gokuldham Co-operative Society and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - revolves around 'Jethalal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Shailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi / Raj Anadkat). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu.
